                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2342b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-31T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5754. The following is the full text of a memorandum relating to the consortium
                    which was delivered to the Japanese Chargé d’Affaires here on July 30:</p>
                <p>[Here follows the memorandum printed <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>]</p>
                <p>You may hand a copy of the above to the Foreign Office and suggest the
                    desirability of representations to the same effect by the British Government.
                    Please report results. Repeat to Embassy Paris for like action and for the
                    information of the American Mission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
